{"lemma":"خَلَّ","slug":"خَلَّ","root":"خ.ل.ل","root_slug":"خ-ل-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ل-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"خَلَّ","root":"خلو","pos":"V","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":7,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":11},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n11166","n11167","n11168"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"vinegar"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"evil, ill","tags":["figuratively","obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become lean or scanty"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pierce, to transfix"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of خَلَّ (ḵalla) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"path through sandy ground"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"an oblong tract of sand"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a vein of the neck and back"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"worn garment"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"camel in the second year"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"friend (male or female)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Aramaic חָלָא / ܚܠܐ (ḥallā, “vinegar”), from Akkadian 𒂁𒄬 (/⁠ḫallu⁠/), from Sumerian 𒂁𒄬 (/⁠ḫal⁠/, “pot; earthen container for storing liquids”).\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n11166","headword_ar":"خَلٌّ","root":"xl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a word of well-known meaning, (S, Msb.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Vinegar;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expressed juice of grapes"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, Mgh, K) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of dates"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"&c."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has become acid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, * Mgh, K:) so called because its sweet flavour has become altered for the worse ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aixotal~a","text_ar":"اِخْتَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (Msb:) a genuine Arabic word: (IDrd, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the best is that of wine: it is composed of two constituents"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of subtile natures,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hot and cold,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the cold being predominant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and is good for the stomach; and for the gums,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which it strengthens, when one rinses the mouth with it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and for foul ulcers"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sores; and for the itch; and for the bite,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sting, of venomous reptiles; and as an antidote for the eating of opium; and for burns; and for toothache; and its hot vapour is good for the dropsy, and for difficulty of hearing, and for ringing in the ears:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K: [various other properties &c. are assigned to it in the TA:]) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xal~apN","text_ar":"خَلَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"somewhat"},{"kind":"text","text":"(lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a portion"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[being the n. un.:] (Aboo-Ziyád, K;) or it may be a dial. var. thereof, like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xamorapN","text_ar":"خَمْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [said by some to be] of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xamorN","text_ar":"خَمْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Aboo-Ziyád, TA:) see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xal~apN","text_ar":"خَلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuluwlN","text_ar":"خُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sorts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kinds, of vinegar"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niEoma AlA_idaAmu Alxal~u","text_ar":"نِعْمَ الاـِدَامُ الخَلُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Excellent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most excellent, is the seasoning, vinegar!"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u Alxal~i","text_ar":"اُمُّ الخَلِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The mother of vinegar;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wine."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, TA.) ―         -b3-  [Hence also the saying,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA fulaAnN bixal~K walaA xamorK","text_ar":"مَا فُلَانٌ بِخَلٍّ وَلَا خَمْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A'Obeyd, JK, S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA lahu xal~N walaA xamorN","text_ar":"مَا لَهُ خَلٌّ وَلَا خَمْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA Einoda","text_ar":"مَا عِنْدَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnK xal~N walaA xamorN","text_ar":"فُلَانٍ خَلٌّ وَلَا خَمْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xmr","text_ar":"خمر"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he, possesses neither good nor evil:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, JK, S, K:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"neither evil nor good:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for] AA says that some of the Arabs make"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxamoru","text_ar":"الخَمْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxal~u","text_ar":"الخَلُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and thus the latter is explained in one place, in this art., in the K;] and some of them make"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxmr","text_ar":"الخمر"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxl~","text_ar":"الخلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 153.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoDN","text_ar":"حَمْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of plants in which is saltness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"salt and bitter plants:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"salt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sour, plants"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trees:"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xul~apN","text_ar":"خُلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"layosato mina Alxal~i walaA AlximaATi"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She is not,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they are not, of the plants"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trees called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xl~","text_ar":"خلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xmAT","text_ar":"خماط"},{"kind":"text","text":"(pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xamoTN","text_ar":"خَمْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")]. (TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A road in sands:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a road passing through sands:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a road between two tracts of sand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a road passing through heaped-up sands:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, K:) masc. and fem. [like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TariyqN","text_ar":"طَرِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, K:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axol~N","text_ar":"اَخْلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xilaAlN","text_ar":"خِلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) One says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hay~apu xal~K","text_ar":"حَيَّةُ خَلٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A serpent of a road in sands,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; like as one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEaY SariymapK","text_ar":"اَفْعَى صَرِيمَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An oblong tract of sand."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 709.) ―         -b3-  ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A vein in the neck"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and in the back,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"communicating with the head."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A slit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rent, in a garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An old and worn-out garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which are streaks:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [or so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobN","text_ar":"ثَوْبٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xal~N","text_ar":"خَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaloxalN","text_ar":"خَلْخَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaloxalN","text_ar":"خَلْخَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a garment, or piece of cloth, (JK, K,) signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"old and worn out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"halohalN","text_ar":"هَلْهَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"halohaAlN","text_ar":"هَلْهَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bird having no feathers:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having few feathers."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-  A man (JK, S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lean, meagre,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"emaciated;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliylN","text_ar":"خَلِيلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) [a meaning said in the TA to be tropical] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxoluwlN","text_ar":"مَخْلُولٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muxotal~N","text_ar":"مُخْتَلٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light in body:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, TA:) and [the fem.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xal~apN","text_ar":"خَلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a woman,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in body, lean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spare:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xal~N","text_ar":"خَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuluwlN","text_ar":"خُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (JK.) Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus bearing two contr. significations: (K:) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxoluwlN","text_ar":"مَخْلُولٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) It is applied to a man and a camel. (TA.) Accord. to the K, it also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young camel such as is termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faSiyl","text_ar":"فَصِيل"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) but it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is lean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"emaciated:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxoluwlN","text_ar":"مَخْلُولٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fSyl","text_ar":"فصيل"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an epithet, for a reason mentioned above, in an explanation of the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xal~a AlfaSiyla","text_ar":"خَلَّ الفَصِيلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, TA.) ―         -b4-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu maxaADK","text_ar":"اِبْنُ مَخَاضٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A male camel in his second year"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (JK, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xal~apN","text_ar":"خَلَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; which is also applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu labuwnK","text_ar":"اِبْنُ لَبُونٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a male camel in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"entering upon, his third year"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and in like manner ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xal~apN","text_ar":"خَلَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK;) or, as in the M, to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a she-camel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) and, as some say, (JK,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a large she-camel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu","text_ar":"اِبْنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxal~api","text_ar":"الخَلَّةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu All~abuwni","text_ar":"اِبْنُ اللَّبُونِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bnY","text_ar":"بنى"},{"kind":"text","text":") or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu maxaADK","text_ar":"اِبْنُ مَخَاضٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abn AlmaxaADi","text_ar":"ابن المَخَاضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA in that art.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ataAhumo biquroSK kaA^an~ahu firosinu","text_ar":"اَتَاهُمْ بِقُرْصٍ كَاَنَّهُ فِرْسِنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xal~apK","text_ar":"خَلَّةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaA^an~ahu xuf~u xal~apK","text_ar":"كَاَنَّهُ خُفُّ خَلَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They brought them a round cake of bread as though it were the foot of a camel in its second,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"third, year,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK. [In the TA, meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samiynap","text_ar":"سَمِينَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fat"},{"kind":"text","text":"); but this seems to be a mistranscription.])       -A5-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cautery."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["JK","Mgh","K","Msb","IDrd","TA","S","As"]},{"entry_id":"n11167","headword_ar":"خُلٌّ","root":"xl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliylN","text_ar":"خَلِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n11168","headword_ar":"خِلٌّ","root":"xl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xul~apN","text_ar":"خُلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places: ―         -b2-  and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliylN","text_ar":"خَلِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in four places."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}